{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870192060,"sessionID":"ses_285e38c63ffeXF4Ja0wABK15Em","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1ca51a001oPhwQyWsWR1JDS","messageID":"msg_d7a1c97b9001KFxpy1Apt84qdk","sessionID":"ses_285e38c63ffeXF4Ja0wABK15Em","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_2d54652723ca452c948940eb","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n2: \n3: ## Summary\n4: \n5: Implement `AgentRuntimeClient` for the AgentCube Python SDK, enabling programmatic invocation of AgentRuntime workloads through the Router data plane with session bootstrap and JSON payload handling.\n6: \n7: ## Purpose\n8: \n9: ### Background\n10: \n11: AgentCube infrastructure consists of:\n12: - **Control Plane (Workload Manager)**: Session lifecycle management\n13: - **Data Plane (Router)**: Code execution and agent invocation\n14: \n15: The `AgentRuntimeClient` complements `CodeInterpreterClient` (AR-027) by providing:\n16: 1. Session bootstrapping via GET request to read `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n17: 2. JSON payload invocation via POST with session header\n18: 3. Context manager support for proper resource cleanup\n19: \n20: ### Goal\n21: \n22: Extend the Python SDK (`agentcube-sdk`) with `AgentRuntimeClient` that:\n23: - Bootstraps session_id from the Router invocation endpoint\n24: - Supports session reuse via constructor argument\n25: - Provides clean context manager protocol\n26: - Follows existing SDK patterns (timeouts, logging, error handling)\n27: \n28: ### Value\n29: \n30: - **Unified SDK**: Single package for both Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime\n31: - **Developer Experience**: Familiar high-level API\n32: - **Reliability**: Built-in session management, timeout handling\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## Scope\n37: \n38: ### In-Scope\n39: \n40: | Component | Path | Description |\n41: |-----------|------|-------------|\n42: | AgentRuntimeClient | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | High-level client API |\n43: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Router communication |\n44: | Session bootstrap | `bootstrap_session_id()` | GET header extraction |\n45: | Invoke | `invoke()` | POST JSON payload |\n46: | Context manager | `__enter__`/`__exit__` | Resource cleanup |\n47: \n48: ### Out-of-Scope\n49: \n50: - Changes to Control Plane (already covered in AR-027)\n51: - Authentication beyond existing token mechanism\n52: - Async support (future enhancement)\n53: - Non-Python SDKs\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Impact Analysis\n58: \n59: ### Dependencies\n60: \n61: | Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n62: |------------|---------|--------|\n63: | `requests` | HTTP client | Required (from AR-027) |\n64: | `PyJWT>=2.0.0` | JWT handling | Required (from AR-027) |\n65: | `cryptography` | Crypto operations | Required (from AR-027) |\n66: \n67: ### Upstream\n68: \n69: - `python-sdk/design.md` ŌĆö Design specification\n70: - `python-sdk/spec.md` ŌĆö Requirements (AgentRuntimeClient sections)\n71: - AR-027 ŌĆö CodeInterpreterClient foundation\n72: \n73: ### Downstream Consumers\n74: \n75: 1. **Python developers** ŌĆö Invoking agent workloads\n76: 2. **Agent orchestration** ŌĆö Chaining multiple agent invocations\n77: 3. **Internal services** ŌĆö Agent execution workflows\n78: \n79: ### Risks\n80: \n81: | Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n82: |------|----------|------------|\n83: | Router unavailable | Medium | Clear error messages, timeout handling |\n84: | Missing session header | Medium | ValueError with specific message |\n85: | Session expiration | Medium | Proper timeout handling |\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: ## Alternatives Considered\n90: \n91: ### Option 1: Reuse CodeInterpreterClient structure (Not Selected)\n92: \n93: **Pros**: Familiar pattern\n94: **Cons**: Different use case (code execution vs agent invocation); separate concerns\n95: \n96: ### Option 2: Generic \"AgentClient\" base class (Not Selected)\n97: \n98: **Pros**: Code sharing\n99: **Cons**: Over-engineering; clients have different initialization paths\n100: \n101: ### Option 3: Standalone AgentRuntimeClient (Selected)\n102: \n103: **Pros**: Clear separation, follows existing SDK structure, easier to maintain\n104: **Cons**: Some code duplication with CodeInterpreterClient patterns\n105: \n106: ### Option 4: Use existing HTTP libraries (httpx, aiohttp) (Not Selected)\n107: \n108: **Pros**: Async support potential\n109: **Cons**: Adds dependency; `requests` sufficient for sync use case\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## Technical Design\n114: \n115: ### AgentRuntimeClient\n116: \n117: ```python\n118: class AgentRuntimeClient:\n119:     def __init__(\n120:         self,\n121:         agent_name: str,\n122:         namespace: str = \"default\",\n123:         router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n124:         verbose: bool = False,\n125:         session_id: Optional[str] = None,\n126:         timeout: int = 120,\n127:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n128:     ): ...\n129: \n130:     def __enter__(self): ...\n131:     def __exit__(self, exc_type, exc_val, exc_tb) -> None: ...\n132: \n133:     def invoke(self, payload: Dict[str, Any], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> Any: ...\n134: \n135:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n136: ```\n137: \n138: ### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n139: \n140: ```python\n141: class AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n142:     SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n143: \n144:     def __init__(\n145:         self,\n146:         router_url: str,\n147:         namespace: str,\n148:         agent_name: str,\n149:         timeout: int = 120,\n150:         connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n151:         pool_connections: int = 10,\n152:         pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n153:     ): ...\n154: \n155:     def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n156: \n157:     def invoke(\n158:         self,\n159:         session_id: str,\n160:         payload: Dict[str, Any],\n161:         timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n162:     ) -> requests.Response: ...\n163: \n164:     def close(self) -> None: ...\n165: ```\n166: \n167: ### Session Bootstrap Flow\n168: \n169: 1. Client initialized with `agent_name`, `namespace`, `router_url`\n170: 2. If `session_id` not provided, call `bootstrap_session_id()`:\n171:    - GET `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n172:    - Extract `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n173:    - Raise `ValueError` if header missing\n174: 3. Store `session_id` for subsequent `invoke()` calls\n175: \n176: ### Invocation Flow\n177: \n178: 1. `invoke(payload, timeout)` validates `session_id` is set\n179: 2. POST to base invocation URL with:\n180:    - Header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n181:    - Header: `Content-Type: application/json`\n182:    - Body: `json=payload`\n183: 3. Return response (caller handles JSON parsing)\n184: \n185: ### Session Header\n186: \n187: All Router requests include:\n188: ```\n189: x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}\n190: ```\n191: \n192: ### Timeout Defaults\n193: \n194: - Read timeout: 120 seconds\n195: - Connect timeout: 5.0 seconds\n196: - Per-call override supported\n197: \n198: ---\n199: \n200: ## Implementation Plan\n201: \n202: ### Phase 1: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n203: \n204: - [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n205: - [ ] Implement `__init__` with router URL construction\n206: - [ ] Implement `bootstrap_session_id()` ŌĆö GET + header extraction\n207: - [ ] Implement `invoke()` ŌĆö POST JSON with session header\n208: - [ ] Implement `close()` ŌĆö HTTP session cleanup\n209: \n210: ### Phase 2: AgentRuntimeClient\n211: \n212: - [ ] Create `agentcube/agent_runtime.py`\n213: - [ ] Implement `__init__` with session_id bootstrap\n214: - [ ] Implement `invoke()` ŌĆö delegate to data plane\n215: - [ ] Implement context manager (`__enter__`/`__exit__`)\n216: - [ ] Implement `close()` ŌĆö delegate to data plane\n217: \n218: ### Phase 3: Integration\n219: \n220: - [ ] Update `agentcube/__init__.py` exports\n221: - [ ] Add examples (`examples/agent_runtime_usage.py`)\n222: - [ ] Add tests\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: ## Acceptance Criteria\n227: \n228: | ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n229: |----|----------|-----------------|\n230: | AR-001 | Context manager exit | HTTP session closed |\n231: | AR-002 | Bootstrap without router | Uses ROUTER_URL env var |\n232: | AR-003 | Bootstrap missing session header | ValueError: \"Missing required response header: x-agentcube-session-id\" |\n233: | AR-004 | Invoke without session_id | ValueError: \"AgentRuntime session_id is not initialized\" |\n234: | AR-005 | Invoke with timeout | Uses (connect_timeout, timeout) tuple |\n235: | AR-006 | POST with correct headers | x-agentcube-session-id + Content-Type: application/json |\n236: \n237: ---\n238: \n239: ## Timeline Estimate\n240: \n241: | Phase | Effort |\n242: |-------|--------|\n243: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | 2 hours |\n244: | AgentRuntimeClient | 1.5 hours |\n245: | Integration & Tests | 2 hours |\n246: | **Total** | **5.5 hours** |\n247: \n248: ---\n249: \n250: ## Relationship to AR-027\n251: \n252: AR-027 (SDK CodeInterpreterClient) provides the foundation:\n253: - Package structure\n254: - Exception hierarchy\n255: - Utility modules\n256: - HTTP session management\n257: \n258: AR-028 extends this foundation with AgentRuntime-specific client, sharing:\n259: - `requests.Session` with pooling\n260: - Timeout conventions\n261: - Logger pattern\n262: - Exception classes\n\n(End of file - total 262 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-028: SDK AgentRuntimeClient\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement `AgentRuntimeClient` for the AgentCube Python SDK, enabling programmatic invocation of AgentRuntime workloads through the Router data plane with session bootstrap and JSON payload handling.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nAgentCube infrastructure consists of:\n- **Control Plane (Workload Manager)**: Session lifecycle management\n- **Data Plane (Router)**: Code execution and agent invocation\n\nThe `AgentRuntimeClient` complements `CodeInterpreterClient` (AR-027) by providing:\n1. Session bootstrapping via GET request to read `x-agentcube-session-id` header\n2. JSON payload invocation via POST with session header\n3. Context manager support for proper resource cleanup\n\n### Goal","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775870192040,"end":1775870192057}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775870192085,"sessionID":"ses_285e38c63ffeXF4Ja0wABK15Em","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1ca9bb001cCX5SWxOIEuoIJ","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7a1c97b9001KFxpy1Apt84qdk","sessionID":"ses_285e38c63ffeXF4Ja0wABK15Em","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":21110,"input":213,"output":86,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":20811}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775870196697,"sessionID":"ses_285e38c63ffeXF4Ja0wABK15Em","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1cbbd7001DLXqxXq4wGjvW2","messageID":"msg_d7a1ca9ec001mzqf9H3LQKmfqN","sessionID":"ses_285e38c63ffeXF4Ja0wABK15Em","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775870250207,"sessionID":"ses_285e38c63ffeXF4Ja0wABK15Em","part":{"id":"prt_d7a1ccb38001QCx4MM7y3oGve1","messageID":"msg_d7a1ca9ec001mzqf9H3LQKmfqN","sessionID":"ses_285e38c63ffeXF4Ja0wABK15Em","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_bb38b61804d6444db986c237","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-029: SDK HTTP Õ║ĢÕ▒éÕ«óµłĘń½»\n\n## Summary\n\nImplement the HTTP client layer for the AgentCube Python SDK, providing low-level HTTP communication for Control Plane (Workload Manager) and Data Plane (Router) operations with connection pooling, timeout management, and session header handling.\n\n## Purpose\n\n### Background\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK requires reliable HTTP communication with two backend services:\n\n- **Control Plane (Workload Manager)**: Session lifecycle (create/delete code interpreter sessions)\n- **Data Plane (Router)**: Code execution, file operations, and agent invocations\n\nThe HTTP layer must handle:\n1. Connection pooling for efficient resource usage\n2. Configurable timeouts (connect + read)\n3. Authentication token injection\n4. Session header management (`x-agentcube-session-id`)\n5. Error handling with appropriate exceptions\n\n### Goal\n\nImplement a robust HTTP client layer that:\n- Provides `ControlPlaneClient` for Workload Manager communication\n- Provides `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient` and `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient` for Router communication\n- Handles connection pooling with `requests.Session` and `HTTPAdapter`\n- Manages timeouts consistently across all clients\n- Follows the SDK's HTTP contract specifications\n\n### Value\n\n- **Reliability**: Consistent timeout and error handling\n- **Performance**: Connection pooling reduces latency\n- **Maintainability**: Centralized HTTP logic\n- **Developer Experience**: Clear API contracts\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In-Scope\n\n| Component | Path | Description |\n|-----------|------|-------------|\n| ControlPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | Workload Manager HTTP client |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | Router CI operations |\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Router agent invocation |\n| create_session | `agentcube/utils/http.py` | Session with pooling |\n| read_token_from_file | `agentcube/utils/utils.py` | Token file reading |\n| Exception classes | `agentcube/exceptions.py` | Error types |\n\n### Out-of-Scope\n\n- High-level client implementations (CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient)\n- Async HTTP support\n- Retry logic / circuit breaker\n- Authentication beyond token file\n\n---\n\n## Impact Analysis\n\n### Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Purpose | Status |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| `requests` | HTTP client | Required |\n| `PyJWT>=2.0.0` | JWT handling | Required |\n| `cryptography` | Crypto operations | Required |\n\n### Upstream\n\n- `python-sdk/design.md` ŌĆö HTTP client specifications\n- `python-sdk/spec.md` ŌĆö HTTP contract requirements\n\n### Downstream Consumers\n\n1. **CodeInterpreterClient** ŌĆö Uses ControlPlaneClient and CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n2. **AgentRuntimeClient** ŌĆö Uses AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n3. **SDK users** ŌĆö Indirect consumers through high-level clients\n\n### Risks\n\n| Risk | Severity | Mitigation |\n|------|----------|------------|\n| Workload Manager unavailable | Medium | Timeout handling, clear error messages |\n| Token file missing | Low | Empty token (anonymous), warning log |\n| Connection pool exhaustion | Medium | Configurable pool size |\n\n---\n\n## Alternatives Considered\n\n### Option 1: httpx for async support (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Native async/await, sync/async unified API\n**Cons**: Adds new dependency; sync `requests` sufficient for current needs\n\n### Option 2: urllib3 directly (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Lower-level control\n**Cons**: More boilerplate; `requests` provides better abstraction\n\n### Option 3: aiohttp (Not Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Async-first design\n**Cons**: Async not in scope; different API paradigm\n\n### Option 4: requests with HTTPAdapter (Selected)\n\n**Pros**: Existing dependency, connection pooling, familiar API, timeout handling\n**Cons**: Sync-only\n\n---\n\n## Technical Design\n\n### HTTP Session Creation\n\n```python\ndef create_session(\n    pool_connections: int = 10,\n    pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n) -> requests.Session:\n    \"\"\"Create requests.Session with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\"\"\"\n```\n\nMounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` schemes.\n\n### ControlPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass ControlPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        workload_manager_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        auth_token: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ): ...\n\n    def create_session(\n        self,\n        name: str = \"my-interpreter\",\n        namespace: str = \"default\",\n        metadata: Optional[Dict[str, Any]] = None,\n        ttl: int = 3600,\n    ) -> str: ...\n\n    def delete_session(self, session_id: str) -> bool: ...\n\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n#### Control Plane HTTP Contract\n\n| Method | Path | Notes |\n|--------|------|-------|\n| POST | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter` | JSON body: `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `metadata` |\n| DELETE | `{base_url}/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | 404 treated as success |\n\n**Headers:**\n- `Content-Type`: `application/json`\n- `Authorization`: `Bearer {token}` if token non-empty\n\n**Timeout:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` on each request.\n\n**URL Resolution:**\n- `base_url` ŌåÉ `workload_manager_url` or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env var\n\n**Token Resolution:**\n- `auth_token` or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n\n### CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient:\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        router_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        namespace: Optional[str] = None,\n        cr_name: Optional[str] = None,\n        base_url: Optional[str] = None,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ): ...\n\n    def _request(self, method: str, endpoint: str, body: Optional[bytes] = None, **kwargs) -> requests.Response: ...\n\n    def execute_command(self, command: Union[str, List[str]], timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n    def run_code(self, language: str, code: str, timeout: Optional[float] = None) -> str: ...\n    def write_file(self, content: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n    def upload_file(self, local_path: str, remote_path: str) -> None: ...\n    def download_file(self, remote_path: str, local_path: str) -> None: ...\n    def list_files(self, path: str = \".\") -> Any: ...\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n#### Data Plane (Code Interpreter) HTTP Contract\n\n**Base URL:**\n- If `base_url` provided: use directly\n- Otherwise: `{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/`\n\n| Method | Relative path | Body / params |\n|--------|---------------|---------------|\n| POST | `api/execute` | JSON `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` |\n| POST | `api/files` | JSON `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` |\n| POST | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` |\n| GET | `api/files/{clean_path}` | `stream=True` for download |\n| GET | `api/files` | query `path` |\n\n**Headers:**\n- Default session header: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n- JSON requests: `Content-Type: application/json`\n- Multipart upload: `x-agentcube-session-id` only\n\n**Note:** Router handles JWT; SDK does not set `Authorization` on data plane.\n\n### AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n```python\nclass AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient:\n    SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"\n\n    def __init__(\n        self,\n        router_url: str,\n        namespace: str,\n        agent_name: str,\n        timeout: int = 120,\n        connect_timeout: float = 5.0,\n        pool_connections: int = 10,\n        pool_maxsize: int = 10,\n    ): ...\n\n    def bootstrap_session_id(self) -> str: ...\n\n    def invoke(\n        self,\n        session_id: str,\n        payload: Dict[str, Any],\n        timeout: Optional[float] = None,\n    ) -> requests.Response: ...\n\n    def close(self) -> None: ...\n```\n\n#### Data Plane (Agent Runtime) HTTP Contract\n\n**Base URL:**\n`{router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/`\n\n| Method | URL | Headers | Body |\n|--------|-----|---------|------|\n| GET | `self.base_url` | (session default headers only) | ŌĆö |\n| POST | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | `json=payload` |\n\n**Timeouts:** `(connect_timeout, timeout)` where `timeout` for `invoke` read side is method argument or `self.timeout`.\n\n### Token File Reading\n\n```python\ndef read_token_from_file(file_path: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Read token from file, return stripped contents or empty string on error.\"\"\"\n```\n\nReturns file contents stripped, or `\"\"` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n\n### Exception Hierarchy\n\n```python\nclass AgentCubeError(Exception):\n    \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n    def __init__(self, exit_code, stderr, command=None):\n        self.exit_code = exit_code\n        self.stderr = stderr\n        self.command = command\n        super().__init__(f\"Command failed (exit {exit_code}): {stderr}\")\n\nclass SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when session creation or management fails\"\"\"\n    pass\n\nclass DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n    \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n    pass\n```\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Core HTTP Utilities\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/utils/http.py` ŌĆö `create_session()` with HTTPAdapter\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/utils/utils.py` ŌĆö `read_token_from_file()`\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/utils/log.py` ŌĆö `get_logger()`\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` ŌĆö empty module marker\n\n### Phase 2: Exception Classes\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/exceptions.py` ŌĆö exception hierarchy\n- [ ] Define `AgentCubeError`, `CommandExecutionError`, `SessionError`, `DataPlaneError`\n\n### Phase 3: ControlPlaneClient\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/__init__.py`\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`\n- [ ] Implement `create_session()` ŌĆö POST to Workload Manager\n- [ ] Implement `delete_session()` ŌĆö DELETE with 404-as-success handling\n- [ ] Implement token resolution (arg/env/file)\n- [ ] Add timeout handling\n\n### Phase 4: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`\n- [ ] Implement base URL construction\n- [ ] Implement `_request()` ŌĆö low-level HTTP\n- [ ] Implement `execute_command()` ŌĆö POST to api/execute\n- [ ] Implement `write_file()` ŌĆö base64 upload\n- [ ] Implement `upload_file()` ŌĆö multipart upload\n- [ ] Implement `download_file()` ŌĆö streaming download\n- [ ] Implement `list_files()` ŌĆö GET with query\n- [ ] Add session header management\n\n### Phase 5: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`\n- [ ] Implement base URL construction\n- [ ] Implement `bootstrap_session_id()` ŌĆö GET + header extraction\n- [ ] Implement `invoke()` ŌĆö POST JSON with session header\n- [ ] Add timeout handling\n\n### Phase 6: Integration & Exports\n\n- [ ] Update `agentcube/clients/__init__.py` exports\n- [ ] Verify all clients work together\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| ID | Scenario | Expected Result |\n|----|----------|-----------------|\n| HTTP-001 | create_session with pooling | Session has HTTPAdapter mounted |\n| HTTP-002 | ControlPlaneClient create_session | POST with correct JSON body, returns sessionId |\n| HTTP-003 | ControlPlaneClient delete_session (404) | Returns True |\n| HTTP-004 | ControlPlaneClient token from file | Reads from default Kubernetes path |\n| HTTP-005 | DataPlaneClient execute_command | POST with correct JSON, timeout handling |\n| HTTP-006 | DataPlaneClient write_file | POST with base64 content |\n| HTTP-007 | DataPlaneClient upload_file | Multipart POST with session header |\n| HTTP-008 | DataPlaneClient download_file | Streaming GET |\n| HTTP-009 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient bootstrap | GET extracts x-agentcube-session-id |\n| HTTP-010 | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient invoke | POST with correct headers |\n| HTTP-011 | Timeout tuple format | (connect_timeout, read_timeout) |\n| HTTP-012 | Session header case | Lowercase `x-agentcube-session-id` |\n\n---\n\n## Timeline Estimate\n\n| Phase | Effort |\n|-------|--------|\n| Core HTTP Utilities | 1 hour |\n| Exception Classes | 0.5 hours |\n| ControlPlaneClient | 1.5 hours |\n| CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | 2.5 hours |\n| AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | 1.5 hours |\n| Integration & Tests | 2 hours |\n| **Total** | **9 hours** |\n\n---\n\n## Relationship to AR-027 / AR-028\n\nAR-027 (SDK CodeInterpreterClient) and AR-028 (SDK AgentRuntimeClient) are high-level clients that consume this HTTP layer.\n\nAR-029 provides the foundation:\n- Connection pooling\n- Timeout management\n- HTTP contracts\n- Session header handling\n- Error types\n\nThe high-level clients delegate HTTP operations to these low-level clients, providing developer-friendly APIs on top.","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775870250161,"end":1775870250204}}}}
